Author:
Vol / Page:  2023
Edition:
Quote:  GovZ.ern-ment (g&ubreve.vZ.&etilde.rn-ment), n. [Add.] Government man, an Australian convict, esp. an assigned servant. [Obs.] "A few prisoners, or government men, as the convict servants are uniformly designated by courtesy." J. D. Lang (1834). - Government stroke, the leisurely manner of working thought to be a characteristic of civil servants. [Colloq.]
